      <div class="docs-eyebrow">Admin Panel</div>
      <h1 class="docs-title">Character Profile Template</h1>
      <p class="docs-lead">
        The Character Profile Template defines the fields shown in the character profile card
        that appears next to posts inside episode (in-character) topics. When a member posts
        in a game thread, this card replaces the standard user profile, displaying the
        character's information instead.
      </p>

      <div class="docs-screenshot">
        <img src="/assets/screenshots/admin-character-profile-template.png" alt="Character Profile Template screenshot" />
      </div>

      <h2 class="docs-h2">How it works</h2>
      <p class="docs-p">
        The interface is identical to the Character Template Editor. Each row defines one field;
        the order of rows controls the order fields appear in the in-post profile card.
        The same field type and content type options are available.
      </p>
      <p class="docs-p">
        The key distinction from the <a href="/docs/admin-character-template/" class="docs-link">Character Template</a>
        is context: the <strong>Character Template</strong> defines the full character sheet
        filled in by the player, while the <strong>Character Profile Template</strong> defines
        the compact card visible to all readers next to every post in an episode thread —
        typically a portrait, name, and a handful of key attributes.
      </p>

      <div class="callout">
        The same rules apply as in the Character Template: renaming a <strong>Machine Field
        Name</strong> after characters have been created will disconnect it from stored data.
        Treat machine names as permanent.
      </div>

      <h2 class="docs-h2">Field properties</h2>
      <p class="docs-p">
        All field properties are the same as in the
        <a href="/docs/admin-character-template/" class="docs-link">Character Template Editor</a>.
        Refer to that page for a full description of Machine Field Name, Human Field Name,
        Field Type, Content Field Type, Order, and Width / Height.
      </p>

      <h2 class="docs-h2">Managing fields</h2>

      <div class="field-list">
        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-meta">
            <div class="field-name">Add Field</div>
          </div>
          <div class="field-desc">
            Appends a new blank field row. Fill in all properties before saving.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-meta">
            <div class="field-name">Remove</div>
          </div>
          <div class="field-desc">
            Removes the field from the editor. The change is not permanent until you click <strong>Save</strong>.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-meta">
            <div class="field-name">Save</div>
          </div>
          <div class="field-desc">
            Saves the entire profile template in one go.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
